{
  "texts": [
    "This leads to a difference in contrast between the reverberated and the direct signal that can introduce variations in the difference curves on the same timescale as the quasar intrinsic variations.",
    "These variations are much faster than the usual microlensing timescale and could explain the complex signals present on such shorter timescales.",
    "When a source moves through a caustic network, whose characteristic size is described by θ E, there is a three-way degeneracy that is introduced between the source size, effective velocity, and the mass of the microlenses.",
    "The relation between these parameters is not exact, but can be understood by the following examples.",
    "If we disregard any velocity component, then the source size and microlens mass are obviously degenerate through the ratio r 1/2 /R E that determines the extent of microlensing effects."
  ]
}